(4674, 420, 'event_information', 'RLT Players To Go! troupe presents <em>A Mother Goose Comedy</em>\r\n\r\nBy Patricia Barry Rumble, with student cast from Raleigh Little Theatre\r\n\r\nJoin us at area libraries for a free performance by the RLT Players To Go! troupe of A Mother Goose Comedy. The world-famous, fun-loving Mother Goose is now retired and living in Mother Goose Resort Spa, where she has time to keep active and pursue her favorite hobbies. She gets tweets, texts and even letters from children all over the world wanting to know how she got the ideas for her nursery rhymes. So, using comedy sketches and some audience participation, Mother Goose explains how all her nursery rhyme characters came about – with some energetic new twists!'),
