(7985, 776, 'class_focus', 'How do you create believable characters? Why does a scene become more alive when the characters are so true to life? Discover the sheer joy and gratification that comes with knowing what your character wants, how you\'ll go about getting it, and actually doing it and living in the moment on stage. In a week filled with commedia dell arte, script analysis, and contemporary scene work, student actors will challenge and empower themselves to experience freedom on stage by thinking for themselves as artists, engaging their imaginations, and always moving through scenes with clear purpose. No previous experience necessary.'),
