(8484, 792, 'class_focus', 'This intensive six week theatre program culminates in six performances of Public Works\' The Tempest, an exciting new adaptation of William Shakespeare\'s play adaptation, music and lyrics by Todd Almond and Originally Conceived and Directed by Lear DeBessonet. TOS students attend conservatory classes which include: acting, voice, improvisation, and training in how to analyze and perform Shakespeare\'s text, as well as rehearse for the production.'),
