(329, 3, '2017-02-22 22:24:50', '2017-02-23 02:24:50', 'Kathleen Rudolph  has been working with the Raleigh Little Theatre Education Program for 20 years. She has a BA in Communications and Theatre, with post-graduate training from Lee Strasberg Theatre Institute and Herbert Berghof Studios in New York. Besides being a theatre instructor, Kathleen is an actor, acting coach and director. Recent directing credits include <em>Can Mrs. Claus Save Christmas?</em>, <em>Miss Nelson is Missing!</em> and <em>Don\'t Dress For Dinner</em>. This season, Kathleen will direct <em>Christmas All Over the Place</em>, <em>Ten Minutes Till Christmas</em> and <em>Bring On The Snow!</em> at The Halle Cultural Arts Center, and <em>James and the Giant Peach</em> at RLT.\r\n\r\n919-821-4579 x225\r\n<a href=\"mailto:kathleen@raleighlittletheatre.org\">kathleen@raleighlittletheatre.org</a>', 'Kathleen Rudolph', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'kathleen-rudolph', '', '', '2017-03-04 16:45:18', '2017-03-04 21:45:18', '', 0, 'http://raleighlt.wpengine.com/?post_type=people&#038;p=329', 5, 'people', '', 0),
