(504, 5, '2017-03-08 11:00:56', '2017-03-08 16:00:56', 'Raleigh Little Theatre will be holding auditions for <em>A Piece of My Heart</em> by Shirley Lauro, inspired by the book by Keith Walker, on <strong>Monday, March 20 and Tuesday, March 21</strong>. The production will will be performed in the Gaddy-Goodwin Teaching Theatre and be directed by Mia Self.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><a style=\"color: #ff0000;\" href=\"http://localhost:8000/cast-list-a-piece-of-my-heart/\">The cast list has been posted</a>.</span>\r\n<h4 id=\"pageToc0\">Important dates</h4>\r\n<strong>Auditions</strong>: Monday and Tuesday March 20 and 21 at 7:00pm in the Gaddy Goodwin Teaching Theatre. Registration from 6:30pm. Please <a href=\"http://www.signupgenius.com/go/30e0a4ca4af2babfe3-auditions3\">reserve an audition slot</a>.\r\n\r\n<strong>Callbacks</strong>: Wednesday, March 22 starting at 7:00pm in the Gaddy-Goodwin Teaching Theatre.\r\n\r\n<strong>First cast meeting</strong>: Monday, March 27\r\n\r\n<strong>No conflicts after</strong>: April 27. No more than 4 conflicts for the entire duration of the rehearsal process.\r\n\r\n<strong>Preview</strong>: May 3 and 4\r\n\r\n<strong>Opening</strong>: Friday, May 5\r\n\r\n<strong>Performances</strong>: May 5 – May 21, Gaddy-Goodwin Teaching Theatre\r\n\r\n<strong>Strike</strong>: May 21 following the 3:00pm show. All actors are expected to participate in strike.\r\n<h4>About the Show</h4>\r\nHistorical drama. A powerful, true drama of six women who went to Vietnam: nurses, a Red Cross volunteer and a USO country-western singer. The latter is booked to entertain the troops by an unscrupulous agent. Follow each young woman’s story before, during, and after her tour in the war-torn nation. It was named “The most enduring play on Vietnam in the nation,” by The Vietnam Vets Association.\r\n\r\nFor more information, see the <a href=\"http://raleighlt.wpengine.com/shows/a-piece-of-my-heart/\" target=\"_blank\"><em>A Piece of My Heart</em> show page</a>.\r\n<h4 id=\"pageToc2\">About the roles</h4>\r\nCasting 6 women and 2 men.\r\n\r\nWhile the characters are noted in the text as young women, their ability to tell this story resides within their ability to look back on their lives. I encourage women of all ages, races, and ethnicities to audition for these roles.\r\n\r\n<strong>Martha</strong> – Strong, self-composed, aura of self-discipline, military bearing. A pioneer. Open age/race/ethnicity.\r\n\r\n<strong>MaryJo</strong> – Outgoing with a bubbly personality. A comedienne. A country-western singer and guitarist. Open age/race/ethnicity.\r\n\r\n<strong>Sissy</strong> – Sweet and feminine. She’s warm, gentle and loads of fun. Open age/race/ethnicity.\r\n\r\n<strong>Whitney</strong> – A Vassar graduate. Aristocratic in demeanor. She’s both withdrawn and contained. Open age/race/ethnicity.\r\n\r\n<strong>Leeann</strong> – Strong and determined. She’s both tough and hip. Asian or multi-racial actor, open age.\r\n\r\n<strong>Steele</strong> - Extremely strong with a military bearing. Intelligent with a great sense of humor. A pragmatist. Black or multi-racial actor, open age.\r\n\r\n<strong>Men</strong> – Versatile actor(s) to play multiple roles. Open age/race/ethnicity.\r\n<h4 id=\"pageToc3\">About the Auditions</h4>\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://www.signupgenius.com/go/30e0a4ca4af2babfe3-auditions3\">reserve an audition slot</a> on either one of the audition nights.\r\n\r\nPlease prepare a monologue no longer than one minute in length to perform for the general auditions. Monologues may be comic or dramatic, but should highlight your ability to play vulnerability and connect with others. Please avoid performing monologues from Shakespearean, Greek, or any classic plays written in verse.\r\n\r\n<strong>Update</strong>: Callbacks are not needed. See the note at the top of the page.\r\n\r\nPerusal copies of the scripts will be available for a 48 hour check out from the RLT office which is located in the rear of the building and opened from 10:00am-5:00pm Mon-Fri. Please call the business office to check on availability (919) 821-4579.\r\n\r\nContact Mia Self at <a href=\"mailto:mlself3@ncsu.edu\">mlself3@ncsu.edu</a> with any questions.\r\n<h4 id=\"pageToc4\">Production Team</h4>\r\nDirector: Mia Self\r\n\r\nScenic Designer: Elizabeth Newton\r\n\r\nLighting Designer: Elizabeth Grimes Droessler\r\n\r\nCostume Designer: Vicki Olson\r\n\r\nStage Manager: Karyn Aberts\r\n<h4 id=\"pageToc5\">Audition forms</h4>\r\nInterested in auditioning? Here\'s some forms to fill out and bring with you to auditions:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://localhost:8000/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/AuditionFormAdult.doc\">Sutton/City Series Audition form</a> -- please fill out</li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://localhost:8000/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Piece-Rehearsal-Calendar.docx\">Conflict Calendar for Piece of My Heart</a> -- please list every weeknight or weekend day that you have a conflict.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;', 'Auditions: A Piece of My Heart', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'auditions-a-piece-of-my-heart', '', '', '2017-03-24 15:07:39', '2017-03-24 19:07:39', '', 0, 'http://raleighlt.wpengine.com/?p=504', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(505, 5, '2017-01-18 12:48:32', '2017-01-18 16:48:32', 'RLT is seeking a Technical Director to join our small team of paid full time staff for the five-week Teens Backstage (TBS) summer theatre camp. The TBS Technical Director will be contracted for six weeks, June 12 - July 22, to allow for one week of preparation prior to camp beginning.\r\n\r\nDuties will include but are not limited to: working with and training 6-9 teens aged 13-17 in a safe scene shop, construction and rigging practices while implementing one fully realized production design in coordination with the Teens on Stage (TOS) summer theatre camp, teach teens how to work from created shop drawings, assist scenic designer in teaching teens painting techniques, assist teens in creating props, and help supervise lighting hang.\r\n\r\nSuccessful candidate should have experience teaching, drafting shop drawings, strong construction skills, experience rigging from fixed grid, and the ability to stay on budget and schedule while still teaching.\r\n\r\nScenic painting and lighting experience a plus. Must pass background check.\r\n\r\nEmail cover letter and resumes to the RLT Production Manager, Todd Aberts, at <a href=\"mailto:todd@ra%6Ceighlittle%74%68e%61tre.org\">todd@raleighlittletheatre.org</a> by April 3, 2017.\r\n\r\nDates: June 12, 2017- July 22, 2017 (6 Weeks)\r\n\r\nPay: $450 per week', 'Seeking a Contract Technical Director for Teens Backstage', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'seeking-a-contract-technical-director-for-teens-backstage', '', '', '2017-02-26 15:30:37', '2017-02-26 19:30:37', '', 0, 'http://raleighlt.wpengine.com/?p=505', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(506, 5, '2017-02-25 12:58:22', '2017-02-25 16:58:22', 'Thinking of auditioning for a show in the 2016-2017 season? Here are the dates for auditions for each show so you can mark your calendars.\r\n<h4>James and the Giant Peach</h4>\r\nAudition Dates: February 27 &amp; 28\r\nShow Dates: April 21 - 30\r\nDirector: Kathleen Rudolph\r\nMore information:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://localhost:8000/shows/james-and-the-giant-peach/\">Show page</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://localhost:8000/2017/01/17/auditions-james-and-the-giant-peach/\">Audition information</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>A Piece of My Heart</h4>\r\nAudition Dates: March 20 &amp; 21\r\nShow Dates: May 5 - 21\r\nDirector: Mia Self\r\nMore information:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://localhost:8000/shows/a-piece-of-my-heart/\">Show page</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://localhost:8000/2017/03/08/auditions-a-piece-of-my-heart/\">Audition information</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Avenue Q</h4>\r\nAudition Dates: April 3 &amp; 4\r\nShow Dates: June 2 - 18\r\nDirector: Jesse R. Gephart\r\nMore information:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://localhost:8000/shows/avenue-q/\">Show page</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://localhost:8000/auditions-avenue-q/\">Audition information</a></li>\r\n</ul>', 'Remaining Audition Dates for 2016-2017 Season', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'remaining-audition-dates-for-2016-2017-season', '', '', '2017-03-21 21:14:02', '2017-03-22 02:14:02', '', 0, 'http://raleighlt.wpengine.com/?p=506', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(509, 5, '2017-02-25 13:28:36', '2017-02-25 17:28:36', 'Come to us or we’ll come to you! <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Our youth education program offers programs that can travel to your school or facility, or exciting opportunities to bring a group on a field trip. </span>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Beyond the Stage Door Field Trips</span></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Raleigh Little Theatre’s award winning education program is proud to offer this exciting drama based field trip. The two hour field trip includes a one-hour workshop and a one-hour backstage tour.</span>\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Theatre Workshop (one hour)</span></h4>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Choose one of these workshop options:</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Stories Alive! Workshop (for grades k-5)</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In this one hour workshop, students will participate in theatre exercises designed to sharpen skills every actor needs including the importance of listening, following directions, supporting others and focusing. Fun theatre exercises help to loosen the body and tighten the brain. Movement exercises help young actors discover how to communicate with their bodies. Finally, the class will bring a story to life using the skills they have learned.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Act It Workshop (for grades 6-8)</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Students will learn the basics of effective communication through physical and vocal expression. Fun theatre games help to reinforce the value of focus and the importance of teamwork.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Lunch option</span></h4>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Between the workshop and the theatre tour, students may choose to take a half hour lunch break. The group supplies the lunches.</span>\r\n<h4>Backstage Tour (one hour)</h4>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Students will get a rare look at the world the audience doesn’t see including the costume shop, dressing rooms, backstage and the scene shop. Students will also get an actor’s view of our stages.</span>\r\n<h4>Cost for a two-hour field trip:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For 10-14 students: $145.00</li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For 15-30 students: $160.00</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If number exceeds 30, we recommend that students be placed in more than one workshop grouping. RLT can accommodate up to 60 children per Field Trip. In the first hour, one group tours while the other attends the Stories Alive Workshop. In the second hour the groups switch.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Dress for Drama! Participants are asked to wear comfortable clothing which allows for freedom of movement and closed toe shoes (like sneakers).</span>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">School Residencies and Workshops</span></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Raleigh Little Theatre is excited to offer theatre based programs to schools.</span>\r\n<h4>Let’s Write a Play!</h4>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Five Day Residency for grades K-5 grade.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In this five day residency, students will learn the building blocks of a story. They will then use “on your feet” theatre exercises to create a story, explore skills for acting out the story, discover ways to reveal character through their bodies and voices and learn ways to turn narration into dialogue. The result is a play of their own which they can rehearse and perform at a later date.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Teachers may choose to create an original fairy tale, a “How Come” story similar to Native American legends or a story which teaches a lesson. RLT teacher may visit 4 classes per day. Exercises are adjusted according to age group, for example the older students may do more work in small groups.</span>\r\n<h4>Stories Alive!</h4>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Workshop for grades K-5</span>\r\n\r\nIn this one hour workshop, students will participate in theatre exercises designed to sharpen skills every actor needs. A brief discussion of the rules helps to reinforce the importance of listening, following directions, supporting others and focus. A check in or introduction exercise invites students to think outside the box and turn on their imaginations. Warm up exercises help loosen the body and tighten (focus) the brain. Movement exercises help young actors learn to communicate with their bodies. Vocal exercises teach students that the tone of their voices says more than the words themselves. Once these are completed the class participates in bringing a story to life.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Teachers may choose from a variety of stories representing different cultures, supporting important character traits or expanding the students understanding of a school topic. The Stories Alive! Program may be offered as a single workshop or a residency according to the needs of the school.</span>\r\n<h4>Books on Stage Literacy Program</h4>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Three Day Residency for grades 1-5.</span>\r\n\r\nThis three day residency uses theatre exercises to promote excitement about reading and improve literacy skills. Using theatre strategies helps to increase comprehension, enjoyment and confidence in emerging readers. Participants are asked to read a selected book prior to artists’ visit. Participants will be able to identify elements of a story (plot, setting, characters, problem, resolution.) More importantly by becoming the characters in the book and reenacting scenes, students gain a better understanding of the book and feel a more personal connection with it. They, the reader, become a very important part of the process.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Book used will be chosen according to age group. Examples are </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Where The Wild Things Are</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> snd </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Miss Nelson is Missing</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. Note: For the school year 2016/2017 for grade 4 we recommend using </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">James and the Giant Peach</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. In April, 2017, Raleigh Little Theatre will present </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">James and the Giant Peach</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> in our Cantey V. Sutton Theatre.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Optional one hour Books On Stage Literacy Program follow up workshop (PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT for teachers) RLT teachers will meet with classroom teachers to unpack the drama based strategies employed during the workshop so they can use the strategies with any story they teach. Additional fee.</span>\r\n<h4>WORDS, WORDS, WORDS: What does Shakespeare really mean?</h4>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Two Day Workshop for grades 6-10 for total 2 hours.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">“To be or not to be, that is the question.” “O Romeo, Romeo, Wherefore art thou Romeo?” Sure these are some of the most famous Shakespeare quotations but what do they mean? Students will explore the magnificence of Shakespeare’s dialogue and text and learn fun tricks for decoding this flowery way of speech. In this workshop, participants will explore the different tools Shakespeare employs in his writing to reveal character, intention, and action for actors.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Through performance and text analysis, participants in this class will learn how Shakespeare uses language to aid our understanding of his great stories, not to confuse us. All examples used during the workshop can be catered to the specific play your class is studying! Students will gain confidence in reading and performing Shakespeare and learn techniques to approach all of his texts.</span>\r\n<h4>Tailor Made Workshops/Residencies</h4>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The teachers at Raleigh Little Theatre will work with schools to design workshops which support curricula and meet the needs of the students. Possibilities include Character Development, Auditioning, Stage Combat and History Alive! Workshops.</span>\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Technical Information</span></h4>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In most cases, RLT’s outreach programs require only a clear open space which allows for freedom of movement. If music is used, access to an outlet is needed.</span>\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Fee Structure:</span></h4>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Workshops: $80.00 per hour</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Stage Combat: $100.00 per hour</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Three Day Residency (12 hours) includes 4 classes per day and one hour planning: $1,010.00</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Five Day Residency (20 hours) includes 4 classes per day and one hour planning: $1,650.00</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Travel Expense: (for locations more than 10 miles from RLT): $10.00 per day.</span>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2>Bookings and more information</h2>\r\nTo schedule a field trip or residency, or to get more information, please contact Meredyth Pederson, Education Director, <a href=\"mailto:meredyth@raleighlittletheatre.org\">meredyth@raleighlittletheatre.org</a>, (919) 821-4579 ext 245.', 'Classes for Schools', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'classes-for-schools', '', '', '2017-03-20 10:20:22', '2017-03-20 15:20:22', '', 7, 'http://raleighlt.wpengine.com/?page_id=509', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(510, 5, '2016-08-09 13:43:43', '2016-08-09 17:43:43', '<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Raleigh Little Theatre is pleased to present adult acting classes designed to develop theatrical skills featured in our season productions to prepare participants for the stage in a safe and nurturing environment. The adult classes are all taught by local theatre professionals with a wealth of experience in the field.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For most of the year, we offer classes that meet on weekly on weekday evenings or on Sunday nights. During the summer, our Evening Summer Intensive Classes offer opportunities for working adults to dive head first into developing and refining theatre skills as we facilitate a full course of study over 5 nights. No prior experience is required. Please, join in the fun!</span>\r\n\r\n<strong>For descriptions of each class and registration information, <a href=\"https://raleighlt.wpengine.com/class-directory?age-group=adults\">visit our adult class directory.</a></strong>', 'Adult Education Program', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'adult-education-program', '', '', '2017-02-26 15:28:54', '2017-02-26 19:28:54', '', 0, 'http://raleighlt.wpengine.com/?p=510', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(511, 5, '2017-02-25 14:01:45', '2017-02-25 18:01:45', '<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">One of three accredited gardens in the Carolinas, the Raleigh Rose Garden at RLT is the display garden for all new roses presented by the All American Rose Society. The grounds include sixty beds with 56 varieties of roses with hybrid teas, floribundas, grandifloras, miniatures and antiques.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-512 size-large\" src=\"http://raleighlt.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Rose-Garden-007-1024x681.jpg\" alt=\"Rose-Garden-007\" width=\"1024\" height=\"681\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Raleigh Rose Garden can be reserved for special occasions and is an ideal spot for smaller, simpler events. Decorations are unnecessary with the parade of roses that bloom from late May until fall\'s first frost in October or November. Both the fountain and the small stone shelter at either end of the garden make lovely back drops for wedding ceremonies and other gatherings.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you are looking for a natural setting with little or no extra decoration, the Raleigh Rose Garden is an excellent choice.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-513 size-full\" src=\"http://raleighlt.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Rose-Garden-016-HDR_edit_web.jpg\" alt=\"Rose-Garden-016-HDR_edit_web\" width=\"900\" height=\"599\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>We are currently taking reservations for events through to December 31, 2017. Interested in reserving the Rose Garden? Download the <a href=\"http://raleighlt.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Rose-Garden-reservations.pdf\">Rose Garden reservations document</a>. </strong>\r\n\r\nFor further information, contact the Special Event Coordinator on Mondays between 9am and noon at Raleigh Little Theatre, 919-821-4579 ext.320 or weddings@raleighlittletheatre.org\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-516 size-large\" src=\"http://raleighlt.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Rose-Garden-021-1024x681.jpg\" alt=\"Rose-Garden-021\" width=\"1024\" height=\"681\" />', 'Rose Garden', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'rose-garden', '', '', '2017-04-05 09:40:08', '2017-04-05 13:40:08', '', 15, 'http://raleighlt.wpengine.com/?page_id=511', 0, 'page', '', 0),
