(556, 5, '2017-02-25 15:39:07', '2017-02-25 19:39:07', 'RLT welcomes people with disabilities to our theater.  Below is information on our organization\'s efforts at ADA accommodations.  For any other questions please contact the RLT business office at 919-821-4579.\r\n<h4>Wheelchair Accessibility</h4>\r\nAll performances are wheelchair accessible. These seats can be seen on the seat map. Please contact the RLT box office at 919-821-3111 for more information.\r\n\r\nClasses may be wheelchair accessible and with two weeks’ notice we are happy to move a class into wheelchair accessible classroom. Please contact Kathleen Rudolph, our Associate Education Director, to discuss your needs 919 821-4579.\r\n<h4>Assistive Listening</h4>\r\nAn induction hearing loop is installed in the Cantey V. Sutton Theatre and can be used in all seats including the balcony. For those without a hearing aid which can tune into the loop, a limited number of assistive listening devices are available on a first come first serve basis.\r\n\r\nAn infrared (IR) system is installed in the Gaddy-Goodwin Teaching Theatre. A limited number of assistive listening devices are available on a first come first serve basis for all performances in this space.\r\n<h4>Service Animals</h4>\r\nTrained service dogs are welcome to attend performances and classes. Trained miniature service horses may be accommodated with two weeks’ notice for classes and if a wheelchair position is available for performances. Miniature horses may not fit into all areas of the building. Please contact the RLT box office at 919-821-3111 for more information.\r\n<h4>Audio Description</h4>\r\nThe following performances will be described, with service provided by Arts Access:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\">One Man, Two Guvnors - Sunday, February 19, 3:00 pm</li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><a href=\"http://raleighlt.wpengine.com/shows/when-she-had-wings/\">When She Had Wings</a> - Sunday, March 26, 5:00 pm</li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><a href=\"http://raleighlt.wpengine.com/shows/james-and-the-giant-peach/\">James and the Giant Peach</a> - Sunday, April 30, 5:00 pm</li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><a href=\"http://raleighlt.wpengine.com/shows/a-piece-of-my-heart/\">A Piece of My Heart</a> - Sunday, May 14, 3:00 pm</li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><a href=\"http://raleighlt.wpengine.com/shows/avenue-q/\">Avenue Q</a> - Sunday, June 11, 3:00 pm</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4><b>American Sign Language Interpretation</b></h4>\r\nPlease contact the RLT box office at 919-821-3111 at least two weeks before opening night of a performance to make arrangements. ASL interpretation of theatrical performances requires specially trained interpreters and rehearsal time. Service provided by Arts Access.\r\n<h4>Scripts</h4>\r\nA limited number of scripts are available to check out prior to attending a performance. Scripts must be returned to and collected from the business office and checkout requires you have a ticket for the performance. Please contact the RLT business office at 919-821-4579 for more information.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-524\" src=\"http://raleighlt.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/arts-access-300x111.png\" alt=\"arts-access\" width=\"300\" height=\"111\" />\r\n\r\nArts Access: Making the arts accessible to persons with disabilities\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Accessibility', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'accessibility', '', '', '2017-02-25 15:39:07', '2017-02-25 19:39:07', '', 15, 'http://raleighlt.wpengine.com/?page_id=556', 0, 'page', '', 0),
