(735, 4, '2017-02-26 21:56:44', '2017-02-27 01:56:44', 'RLT has a <strong>full time staff</strong> of theatre and education professionals. We also contract with a large number of <strong>instructors</strong> to teach our classes and camps year round. And to oversee the operation of the theatre, RLT\'s <strong>board of directors</strong> are committed group of business professionals from our local community.', 'Our Staff', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '11-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-02-26 21:56:44', '2017-02-27 01:56:44', '', 11, 'http://raleighlt.wpengine.com/2017/02/26/11-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(736, 4, '2017-02-26 22:09:40', '2017-02-27 02:09:40', 'Jenny Mitchell is the Associate Costume Designer here at RLT. Her recent Costume Design credits include: <em>The Rivals, The Velveteen Rabbit, Venus in Fur, The Complete Works of Shakespeare (Abridged/Revised), The Rocky Horror Show, The 39 Steps, Sideways Stories from Wayside School, Dear Edwina Jr., Nate the Great, The Miss Firecracker Contest, Merry Christmas Strega Nona, Animal Farm</em> and <em>Junie B. Jones</em>.', 'Jenny Mitchell', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '496-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-02-26 22:09:40', '2017-02-27 02:09:40', '', 496, 'http://raleighlt.wpengine.com/2017/02/26/496-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(737, 5, '2017-02-26 23:59:26', '2017-02-27 03:59:26', 'The Raleigh Little Theatre complex is two blocks west of Cameron Village. Our address is:\r\n\r\n301 Pogue Street\r\nRaleigh, NC 27607\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-738 size-full\" src=\"http://raleighlt.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/map-RLT.gif\" width=\"354\" height=\"402\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-739 size-full\" src=\"http://raleighlt.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/RLT-aerial-annotated.gif\" width=\"706\" height=\"581\" />\r\n<h4>Parking for shows and events</h4>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">RLT has plenty of free parking available to patrons in our off-street parking lot. Entry is via Pogue Street. There is also plenty of on-street parking around the theatre, but please observe the parking restrictions. During performances or special events at the theatre, you may park in any of the spaces marked \"Permit required\", but please respect the spaces reserved for our disabled visitors</span>\r\n<h4>Parking during weekdays</h4>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Some of the spaces in the parking lot have \"Permit Required\" on them. The City of Raleigh does enforce these markings Monday-Friday from 9 am to 5 pm to reduce the number of students parking in our lot and is not enforced during performances or special events at Raleigh Little Theatre.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Some of the spaces have \"20 minute parking Mon-Fri 9am-5pm\". These are for use if you are visiting the theatre for a short period and don\'t wish to park on the street.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For more information about parking and public transportation in the area, visit the </span><a href=\"http://hillsboroughstreet.org/directory/parking-and-transportation\"><b>Hillsborough Street parking and transportation page</b></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span>', 'Maps and Parking', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'maps-and-parking', '', '', '2017-02-28 10:16:31', '2017-02-28 15:16:31', '', 15, 'http://raleighlt.wpengine.com/?page_id=737', 0, 'page', '', 0),
