(770, 3, '2017-02-27 03:00:04', '2017-02-27 07:00:04', 'Naima Yetunde Ince is a spoken word artist who has a BA in Drama Studies and attended SUNY Purchase College where she honed her theatrical skills with focuses as playwright, director and stage manager. Naima has a M.PS (Masters of Professional) in Arts and Cultural Management from Pratt Institute. She has significant accomplishments within the New York City area as a performance poet and also produces and directs theatrical works. A recent resident of Raleigh, Naima recently directed an original one act play entitled Men Always Leave produced by The First Annual Women\'s Theater Festival summer of 2016.', 'Naima Ince', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'naima-ince', '', '', '2017-02-27 15:26:58', '2017-02-27 19:26:58', '', 0, 'http://raleighlt.wpengine.com/?post_type=people&#038;p=770', 46, 'people', '', 0),
