(823, 4, '2017-02-27 12:00:44', '2017-02-27 17:00:44', '[caption id=\"attachment_592\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"599\"]<img class=\"wp-image-592\" src=\"http://raleighlt.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/RLT-Storytellers-Soar-43_small-300x199.jpg\" alt=\"The Storytellers To Go! cast of Soar!\" width=\"599\" height=\"397\" /> The Storytellers To Go! cast of Soar![/caption]\r\n\r\nRaleigh Little Theatre\'s Storytellers to Go! presents<em> Soar! The Hero Pigeons of WWI. </em>Written by Judy M. Dove, <em>Soar!</em> commemorates the 100th anniversary of the United States entering WWI on April 6, 1917, by retelling the true story of Cher Ami, a carrier pigeon who became a war hero.\r\n\r\nThis short play recounts the story of the Lost Battalion, the name given to the U.S. 77th Division, as they were trapped by the Germans in the Argonne Forest in France in October of 1918. The unit was saved by a pigeon who, despite being shot, was able to regain flight to successfully deliver a message for help.\r\n\r\nThe story is told from the pigeons’ perspectives and is appropriate for ages five and older.\r\n\r\nAdmission: Free!\r\nPerformances of <em>Soar!</em> are being offered free of charge as part of RLT\'s community outreach\r\n<h4>PERFORMANCES</h4>\r\n<strong>Saturday, January 14, 3:00pm</strong>\r\nNorth Regional Library, 7009 Harps Mill Rd., Raleigh, NC 27615\r\n\r\n<strong>Saturday, January 21, 3:00pm\r\n</strong>Northeast Regional Library, 14401 Green Elm Lane, Raleigh, NC 27614\r\n\r\n<strong>Saturday, January 28, 3:00pm</strong>\r\nSoutheast Regional Library, 908 7th Avenue, Garner, NC 27529\r\n\r\n<strong>Saturday, February 4, 3:00pm</strong>\r\nWest Regional Library, 4000 Louis Stephens Rd., Cary, NC 27519\r\n\r\n<strong>Saturday, February 11, 3:00pm\r\n</strong>Cameron Village Library, 1930 Clark Avenue, Raleigh, NC 27605\r\n\r\n<strong>Saturday, February 18, 2:00pm\r\n</strong>East Regional Library, 946 Steeple Square Ct., Knightdale, NC 27545\r\n\r\n<strong>Saturday, February 25, 2:00pm\r\n</strong>NC Museum of History, 5 East Edenton Street, Raleigh, NC 27601\r\n\r\n<strong>Saturday, March 4, 3:00pm\r\n</strong>Eva Perry Regional Library, 2100 Shepherds Vineyard Dr, Apex, NC 27502\r\n\r\n<strong>Saturday, March 18, 3:00pm</strong><strong>\r\n</strong>Halle Cultural Arts Center of Apex, 237 N. Salem Street, Apex, NC\r\n<h4>CAST</h4>\r\nStudent Cast from Raleigh Little Theatre\r\n\r\nSOPHIE: <strong>Beth Furry</strong>\r\nREID: <strong>James Sinnott-Nadasky\r\n</strong>ALYSSA: <strong>Caroline Gschwind</strong>\r\nMANNY: <strong>Alyssa Schoaff</strong>\r\nDUSTY: <strong>Megan Dale\r\n</strong>WILLIAM: <strong>Hallie Turner</strong>\r\nYORICK: <strong>Sophie Dubois</strong>\r\nCHER AMI: <strong>Anna Harbin</strong>\r\nHERR FALKE: <strong>Alyssa Schoaff</strong>\r\nMAJOR CHARLES WHITE WHITTLESEY: <strong>James Sinnott-Nadasky\r\n</strong>CAPTAIN GEORGE MCMURTRY: <strong>Beth Furry</strong>', 'Performing at Area Libraries: Soar! The Hero Pigeons of WWI', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'soar-the-hero-pigeons-of-wwi', '', '', '2017-02-27 15:25:34', '2017-02-27 20:25:34', '', 0, 'http://raleighlt.wpengine.com/?p=823', 0, 'post', '', 0);
