(826, 5, '2017-02-27 15:50:36', '2017-02-27 20:50:36', '[caption id=\"attachment_592\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"599\"]<img class=\"wp-image-592\" src=\"http://raleighlt.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/RLT-Storytellers-Soar-43_small-300x199.jpg\" alt=\"The Storytellers To Go! cast of Soar!\" width=\"599\" height=\"397\" /> The Storytellers To Go! cast of Soar![/caption]\r\n\r\nRaleigh Little Theatre\'s Storytellers to Go! presents<em> Soar! The Hero Pigeons of WWI. </em>Written by Judy M. Dove, <em>Soar!</em> commemorates the 100th anniversary of the United States entering WWI on April 6, 1917, by retelling the true story of Cher Ami, a carrier pigeon who became a war hero.\r\n\r\nThis short play recounts the story of the Lost Battalion, the name given to the U.S. 77th Division, as they were trapped by the Germans in the Argonne Forest in France in October of 1918. The unit was saved by a pigeon who, despite being shot, was able to regain flight to successfully deliver a message for help.\r\n\r\nThe story is told from the pigeons’ perspectives and is appropriate for ages five and older.\r\n\r\nAdmission: Free!\r\nPerformances of <em>Soar!</em> are being offered free of charge as part of RLT\'s community outreach\r\n<h4>PERFORMANCES</h4>\r\n<strong>Saturday, January 14, 3:00pm</strong>\r\nNorth Regional Library, 7009 Harps Mill Rd., Raleigh, NC 27615\r\n\r\n<strong>Saturday, January 21, 3:00pm\r\n</strong>Northeast Regional Library, 14401 Green Elm Lane, Raleigh, NC 27614\r\n\r\n<strong>Saturday, January 28, 3:00pm</strong>\r\nSoutheast Regional Library, 908 7th Avenue, Garner, NC 27529\r\n\r\n<strong>Saturday, February 4, 3:00pm</strong>\r\nWest Regional Library, 4000 Louis Stephens Rd., Cary, NC 27519\r\n\r\n<strong>Saturday, February 11, 3:00pm\r\n</strong>Cameron Village Library, 1930 Clark Avenue, Raleigh, NC 27605\r\n\r\n<strong>Saturday, February 18, 2:00pm\r\n</strong>East Regional Library, 946 Steeple Square Ct., Knightdale, NC 27545\r\n\r\n<strong>Saturday, February 25, 2:00pm\r\n</strong>NC Museum of History, 5 East Edenton Street, Raleigh, NC 27601\r\n\r\n<strong>Saturday, March 4, 3:00pm\r\n</strong>Eva Perry Regional Library, 2100 Shepherds Vineyard Dr, Apex, NC 27502\r\n\r\n<strong>Saturday, March 18, 3:00pm</strong><strong>\r\n</strong>Halle Cultural Arts Center of Apex, 237 N. Salem Street, Apex, NC\r\n<h4>CAST</h4>\r\nStudent Cast from Raleigh Little Theatre\r\n\r\nSOPHIE: <strong>Beth Furry</strong>\r\nREID: <strong>James Sinnott-Nadasky\r\n</strong>ALYSSA: <strong>Caroline Gschwind</strong>\r\nMANNY: <strong>Alyssa Schoaff</strong>\r\nDUSTY: <strong>Megan Dale\r\n</strong>WILLIAM: <strong>Hallie Turner</strong>\r\nYORICK: <strong>Sophie Dubois</strong>\r\nCHER AMI: <strong>Anna Harbin</strong>\r\nHERR FALKE: <strong>Alyssa Schoaff</strong>\r\nMAJOR CHARLES WHITE WHITTLESEY: <strong>James Sinnott-Nadasky\r\n</strong>CAPTAIN GEORGE MCMURTRY: <strong>Beth Furry</strong>', 'Performing at Area Libraries: Soar! The Hero Pigeons of WWI', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '823-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-02-27 15:50:36', '2017-02-27 20:50:36', '', 823, 'http://raleighlt.wpengine.com/2017/02/27/823-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(827, 5, '2017-02-27 12:00:52', '2017-02-27 17:00:52', '<strong>Registration for 2017 summer theatre camps is now open! </strong>Now in its 28th year, RLT\'s Education Program provides children ages 4-12 and teenagers with comprehensive theatrical training. Camps will fill up quickly so go online and register soon.\r\n\r\nOur mission is for each student in our program to find his or her voice and sense of play in a non-competitive atmosphere. We believe that drama provides our students with the tools necessary to become not only respectful patrons of the arts, but creative problem solvers, self-confident leaders and effective communicators. The study of theatre not only trains our students to be better actors, it inspires them to be better people.\r\n\r\nOur award-winning education program provides high quality theatre arts instruction to over 900 students each year in a safe and nurturing environment.\r\n\r\n<strong>One-week and two-week camps</strong> focus on the process of creating theatre through fun, imaginative, nurturing creative play and ensemble building. All camps will culminate in an ‘open classroom’ to give parents and friends a taste of the participants’ everyday experience in the program.\r\n\r\n<strong>Teen conservatory programs</strong> give the serious theatre student the opportunity for in-depth exploration in a variety of areas. Conservatory Programs are guided by accomplished program staff and professional guest artists.\r\n<h4>Summer Camps Directory</h4>\r\nFor full descriptions and additional information on each camp and registration information, <a href=\"https://raleighlittletheatre.org/class-directory/?types=summer-camp\">visit the full summer camps directory</a>.\r\n<h4>Registration</h4>\r\nTo register for camps at RLT and Wendell, use our <a href=\"http://www.myloreg.com/orderbooking/go/camps\">online registration facility</a>. If you\'re having trouble with the online facility, you may also register by sending in our <a href=\"http://localhost:8000/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/RLT-Summer2017-RegistrationForm.pdf\">Registration Form</a> (PDF).\r\n\r\nFor Wake Forest and Apex, see the above offsite camp pages for information.\r\n<h4>Summer Intensives for Adults</h4>\r\nWe also offer <a href=\"http://localhost:8000/summer-intensives-for-adults/\">one-week evening classes for Adults</a>. Check out the details!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFor any questions about camps or our online registration, contact:\r\n\r\nKathleen Rudolph\r\nAssociate Education Director\r\n<a href=\"mailto:kathleen@raleighlittletheatre.org\">kathleen@raleighlittletheatre.org</a>\r\n919-821-4579 x 225', 'Summer 2017 Theatre Camps', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'summer-2017-theatre-camps', '', '', '2017-03-28 16:49:44', '2017-03-28 20:49:44', '', 0, 'http://raleighlt.wpengine.com/?p=827', 0, 'post', '', 0),
