(905, 4, '2017-03-22 09:24:32', '2017-03-22 14:24:32', 'Raleigh Little Theatre will be holding auditions for <em>A Piece of My Heart</em> by Shirley Lauro, inspired by the book by Keith Walker, on <strong>Monday, March 20 and Tuesday, March 21</strong>. The production will will be performed in the Gaddy-Goodwin Teaching Theatre and be directed by Mia Self.\n\n<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Update about Calbacks</strong>: Thank you to everyone who auditioned for <em>A Piece of My Heart</em>. As always, we were blown away by the talent and are grateful to our community of artists for their preparation and courage in the audition process. For this production, our director was able to make confident decisions in casting from the general auditions and does not need to have callbacks. <strong>The cast list will be posted by 2 pm this Friday</strong>. If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to contact Patrick Torres at patrick@raleighlittletheatre.org. Thank you!</span>\n<h4 id=\"pageToc0\">Important dates</h4>\n<strong>Auditions</strong>: Monday and Tuesday March 20 and 21 at 7:00pm in the Gaddy Goodwin Teaching Theatre. Registration from 6:30pm. Please <a href=\"http://www.signupgenius.com/go/30e0a4ca4af2babfe3-auditions3\">reserve an audition slot</a>.\n\n<strong>Callbacks</strong>: Wednesday, March 22 starting at 7:00pm in the Gaddy-Goodwin Teaching Theatre.\n\n<strong>First cast meeting</strong>: Monday, March 27\n\n<strong>No conflicts after</strong>: April 27. No more than 4 conflicts for the entire duration of the rehearsal process.\n\n<strong>Preview</strong>: May 3 and 4\n\n<strong>Opening</strong>: Friday, May 5\n\n<strong>Performances</strong>: May 5 – May 21, Gaddy-Goodwin Teaching Theatre\n\n<strong>Strike</strong>: May 21 following the 3:00pm show. All actors are expected to participate in strike.\n<h4>About the Show</h4>\nHistorical drama. A powerful, true drama of six women who went to Vietnam: nurses, a Red Cross volunteer and a USO country-western singer. The latter is booked to entertain the troops by an unscrupulous agent. Follow each young woman’s story before, during, and after her tour in the war-torn nation. It was named “The most enduring play on Vietnam in the nation,” by The Vietnam Vets Association.\n\nFor more information, see the <a href=\"http://raleighlt.wpengine.com/shows/a-piece-of-my-heart/\" target=\"_blank\"><em>A Piece of My Heart</em> show page</a>.\n<h4 id=\"pageToc2\">About the roles</h4>\nCasting 6 women and 2 men.\n\nWhile the characters are noted in the text as young women, their ability to tell this story resides within their ability to look back on their lives. I encourage women of all ages, races, and ethnicities to audition for these roles.\n\n<strong>Martha</strong> – Strong, self-composed, aura of self-discipline, military bearing. A pioneer. Open age/race/ethnicity.\n\n<strong>MaryJo</strong> – Outgoing with a bubbly personality. A comedienne. A country-western singer and guitarist. Open age/race/ethnicity.\n\n<strong>Sissy</strong> – Sweet and feminine. She’s warm, gentle and loads of fun. Open age/race/ethnicity.\n\n<strong>Whitney</strong> – A Vassar graduate. Aristocratic in demeanor. She’s both withdrawn and contained. Open age/race/ethnicity.\n\n<strong>Leeann</strong> – Strong and determined. She’s both tough and hip. Asian or multi-racial actor, open age.\n\n<strong>Steele</strong> - Extremely strong with a military bearing. Intelligent with a great sense of humor. A pragmatist. Black or multi-racial actor, open age.\n\n<strong>Men</strong> – Versatile actor(s) to play multiple roles. Open age/race/ethnicity.\n<h4 id=\"pageToc3\">About the Auditions</h4>\nPlease <a href=\"http://www.signupgenius.com/go/30e0a4ca4af2babfe3-auditions3\">reserve an audition slot</a> on either one of the audition nights.\n\nPlease prepare a monologue no longer than one minute in length to perform for the general auditions. Monologues may be comic or dramatic, but should highlight your ability to play vulnerability and connect with others. Please avoid performing monologues from Shakespearean, Greek, or any classic plays written in verse.\n\n<strong>Update</strong>: Callbacks are not needed. See the note at the top of the page.\n\nPerusal copies of the scripts will be available for a 48 hour check out from the RLT office which is located in the rear of the building and opened from 10:00am-5:00pm Mon-Fri. Please call the business office to check on availability (919) 821-4579.\n\nContact Mia Self at <a href=\"mailto:mlself3@ncsu.edu\">mlself3@ncsu.edu</a> with any questions.\n<h4 id=\"pageToc4\">Production Team</h4>\nDirector: Mia Self\n\nScenic Designer: Elizabeth Newton\n\nLighting Designer: Elizabeth Grimes Droessler\n\nCostume Designer: Vicki Olson\n\nStage Manager: Karyn Aberts\n<h4 id=\"pageToc5\">Audition forms</h4>\nInterested in auditioning? Here\'s some forms to fill out and bring with you to auditions:\n<ul>\n 	<li><a href=\"http://localhost:8000/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/AuditionFormAdult.doc\">Sutton/City Series Audition form</a> -- please fill out</li>\n 	<li><a href=\"http://localhost:8000/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Piece-Rehearsal-Calendar.docx\">Conflict Calendar for Piece of My Heart</a> -- please list every weeknight or weekend day that you have a conflict.</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;', 'Auditions: A Piece of My Heart', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '504-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-03-22 09:24:32', '2017-03-22 14:24:32', '', 504, 'http://localhost:8000/2017/03/11/504-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
