(920, 4, '2017-03-21 21:10:13', '2017-03-22 02:10:13', 'Raleigh Little Theatre will be holding auditions for <em>Avenue Q</em> on Monday, April 3 and Tuesday, April 4 with callbacks on April 5. The production will be directed by Jesse R. Gephart.<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8000/callbacks-for-avenue-q/\">Callbacks have now been posted</a>.\r\n<h3 id=\"pageToc0\">Important dates</h3>\r\n<strong>Auditions</strong>: Monday and Tuesday April 3 and 4 in the Gaddy-Goodwin Teaching Theatre. Registration from 6:30pm and rehearsals start at 7:00pm. Please <a href=\"http://www.signupgenius.com/go/30E0A4CA4AF2BABFE3-auditions4\">sign up for an audition night</a>.\r\n<strong>Callbacks</strong>: April 5 at 7:00 pm in the Gaddy-Goodwin Teaching Theatre\r\n<strong>First cast meeting</strong>: Monday, April 17\r\n<strong>No conflicts after</strong>: May 5. No more than 5 conflicts for the entire duration of the rehearsal process.\r\n\r\n<strong>Preview</strong>: Wednesday, May 31 and Thursday, June 1\r\n<strong>Opening night</strong>: Friday, June 2\r\n<strong>Performances</strong>: June 2 through June 18 with a likely extension to June 25\r\n<strong>Strike</strong>: June 18 (or June 25, if extended) following the 3:00pm show. All actors are expected to participate in strike.\r\n<h3>About the Show</h3>\r\nRecent college grad, Princeton, moves into a shabby New York apartment all the way out on Avenue Q. Along with his new friends, Princeton struggles to find a job, date, and discover an ever-elusive purpose in life. Filled with gut-busting humor and a delightfully catchy score, not to mention puppets, this truly unique show has quickly become a favorite for audiences everywhere.\r\n\r\nFor more information, see the<a href=\"http://localhost:8000/shows/avenue-q/\"><em> Avenue Q</em></a> show page.\r\n<h3 id=\"pageToc2\">About the roles</h3>\r\n<strong>Princeton</strong>:\r\nA fresh-faced kid just out of college and the protagonist. Puppet.\r\nGender: Male\r\nAge: 20 to 25\r\nVocal range top: G4\r\nVocal range bottom: Bb2\r\n\r\n<strong>Kate Monster:</strong>\r\nA Kindergarten teaching assistant, who is a bit older than Princeton. Puppet.\r\nGender: Female\r\nAge: 25 to 30\r\nVocal range top: F5\r\nVocal range bottom: F#3\r\n\r\n<strong>Nicky: </strong>\r\nA slacker who lives with Rod. Puppet.\r\nGender: Male\r\nAge: 20 to 30\r\nVocal range top: B4\r\nVocal range bottom: B2\r\n\r\n<strong>Rod</strong>:\r\nAn investment banker who is Republican and a closeted homosexual. Puppet.\r\nGender: Male\r\nAge: 25 to 30\r\nVocal range top: G4\r\nVocal range bottom: A2\r\n\r\n<strong>Trekkie Monster</strong>:\r\nA reclusive creature obsessed with the Internet and all it has to offer. Puppet.\r\nGender: Male\r\nAge: 30 to 40\r\nVocal range top: Eb4\r\nVocal range bottom: Bb2\r\n\r\n<strong>Lucy</strong>:\r\nA vixenish vamp with a dangerous edge. Puppet.\r\nGender: Female\r\nAge: 25 to 30\r\nVocal range top: F5\r\nVocal range bottom: F3\r\n\r\n<strong>The Bad Idea Bears</strong>:\r\nTwo snuggly, cute teddy-bear types. Puppets.\r\nGender: Female\r\nAge: 20 to 40\r\nVocal range top: G4\r\nVocal range bottom: Bb3\r\n\r\n<strong>Mrs. T</strong>:\r\nCrabby and ancient. Kate\'s boss. Puppet.\r\nGender: Female\r\nAge: 50 to 65\r\n\r\n<strong>Brian</strong>:\r\nA laid-back guy married to Christmas Eve. Human.\r\nGender: Male\r\nAge: 30 to 45\r\nVocal range top: F#4\r\nVocal range bottom: B2\r\n\r\n<strong>Christmas Eve</strong>:\r\nA therapist who recently moved to Avenue Q from Japan. Human.\r\nGender: Female\r\nAge: 30 to 45\r\nVocal range top: F#5\r\nVocal range bottom: B3\r\n\r\n<strong>Gary Coleman</strong>:\r\nYes, that Gary Coleman. Lives on the Avenue and is superintendent of the apartment buildings. Human.\r\nGender: Female\r\nAge: 30 to 40\r\nVocal range top: Bb5\r\nVocal range bottom: D3\r\n<h3 id=\"pageToc3\">About the Auditions</h3>\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://www.signupgenius.com/go/30E0A4CA4AF2BABFE3-auditions4\">sign up for an audition night</a>.\r\n\r\nPlease prepare 16 – 32 bars of a song in the style of the show. Something upbeat and fun, funny, or even quirky. Personality is paramount.\r\n\r\nYou must bring your own sheet music and an accompanist will be provided by the theatre. Please do not perform acapella unless that is how the song you will perform was originally written.\r\n\r\nWe encourage individuals of all ethnicities, abilities, identities, and orientations to audition.\r\n\r\nNote that the traditional tracking of this show may not be used. We are open to exploring how we can remain true to the story and structure, while simultaneously showcasing as much community talent as we can. The solo casting of folks like Rod and Princeton, or Kate Monster and Lucy, as well as a more “non-traditional” ensemble, open up opportunities we are excited to explore if they present themselves.\r\n\r\nCallback list will be posted on the RLT website by Noon on Wednesday, April 5.\r\n\r\nCallbacks: Wednesday, April 5 in the Gaddy-Goodwin Teaching Theatre\r\n\r\nPerusal copies of the scripts will be available for a 48 hour check out from the RLT office which is located in the rear of the building and opened from 10:00am-5:00pm Mon-Fri. Please call the business office to check on availability (919) 821-4579.\r\n\r\nContact Patrick Torres at <a href=\"mailto:patrick@raleighlittletheatre.org\">patrick@raleighlittletheatre.org</a> with any questions.\r\n<h3 id=\"pageToc4\">Production Team</h3>\r\nDirector: Jesse R. Gephart\r\nMusic Director: TBD\r\nScenic Designers: Miyuki Su &amp; Duncan Jenner\r\nLighting Designer: Cailen Waddell\r\nCostume Designer: Vicki Olson\r\nStage Manager: Adam Budlong\r\n<h3>About RLT</h3>\r\nRaleigh Little Theatre is a welcoming community theatre with a large family of volunteer actors and backstage crew. Our staff of designers and directors strive to deliver a professional level of quality to our productions which has resulted in many awards over the years. All our actors and crew members are volunteers and we encourage you to join us!\r\n<h3 id=\"pageToc5\">Audition forms</h3>\r\nInterested in auditioning? Here\'s some forms to fill out and bring with you to auditions:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://localhost:8000/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/AuditionFormAdult.doc\">Sutton/City Series Audition form</a> (DOC) -- please fill out</li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://localhost:8000/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Avenue-Q-Conflict-Calendar.pdf\">Conflict Calendar</a> (PDF)-- please list every weeknight or weekend day that you have a conflict.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Auditions: Avenue Q', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'auditions-avenue-q', '', '', '2017-04-06 21:31:10', '2017-04-07 01:31:10', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=920', 0, 'post', '', 0),
