(961, 4, '2017-03-30 22:29:44', '2017-03-31 02:29:44', '<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-962 size-full\" title=\"Aya Wallace as Felicia and Zak Casca as Huey in the RLT production of &quot;Memphis&quot;, August 2016.\" src=\"http://localhost:8000/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Memphis-022.jpg\" alt=\"Aya Wallace as Felicia and Zak Casca as Huey in the RLT production of &quot;Memphis&quot;, August 2016\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1116\" />\r\n<h4>Our Mission</h4>\r\nRLT is a welcoming community using theatre to enrich, educate, entertain and engage volunteers, students, and audiences of all ages.\r\n<h4>Our Vision</h4>\r\nThree years from now RLT will be:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>A creative hub producing innovative, varied and sought after theatre</li>\r\n 	<li>Providing an increasingly diverse and dynamic education program</li>\r\n 	<li>Supported by an organized and educated volunteer base</li>\r\n 	<li>Financially sustainable</li>\r\n 	<li>Fully utilizing state of the art facilities and technology</li>\r\n 	<li>Actively collaborating with other arts and community organizations</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Our Values</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>A quality theatre experience</li>\r\n 	<li>The power of theatre as an art form</li>\r\n 	<li>A nurturing, safe environment</li>\r\n 	<li>Creativity and individual expression</li>\r\n 	<li>Education and personal growth through theatre</li>\r\n 	<li>Active community engagement</li>\r\n 	<li>Diversity in all areas</li>\r\n 	<li>Respect for our audience</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nApproved by the RLT Board of Directors, April 2013.', 'Our Mission', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'our-mission', '', '', '2017-03-31 06:07:42', '2017-03-31 10:07:42', '', 17, 'http://localhost:8000/?page_id=961', 0, 'page', '', 0),
